as.numeric(data_gasoline\(UGS) as.numeric(data_gasoline\)RNUV) as.numeric(data_gasoline\(NLPG) as.numeric(data_gasoline\)PU) as.numeric(data_gasoline\(PG) as.numeric(data_gasoline\)NUGV) as.numeric(data_gasoline\(GNP.Agriculture) as.numeric(data_gasoline\)GNP.Commerce) as.numeric(data_gasoline$GNP.Total)

#Converting quarters into date objects new_quarter <- seq(as.Date(“2000-01-01”), by=“quarter”, length.out =32) data_gasoline$Quarter <- new_quarter

#Plotting of UGS time series

UGS_time_series<-  ts(data_gasoline$UGS[1:28],start = c(2000,1), frequency = 4 )
plot(UGS_time_series)

#Data seems to has a decreasing trend line, and it is not stationary

 UGS_decomposed <- decompose(UGS_time_series, type="multiplicative") 
plot(UGS_decomposed)

#I will take the difference between observations to obtain a stationary time series

Diff_UGS_time_series <- diff(UGS_time_series)
plot(Diff_UGS_time_series)

#autocorrelation plot shows us at lag 1 and lag 4 acf is out of the boundary which shows us the seasonality effect.

acf(data_gasoline$UGS[1:28], 8)

forecasting

#seasonal naive method, p-value = 9.137e-09, residual SD=223671.49,residuals seem random, all acf is between %95 conf. interval boundaries

snaive_model_1 <- snaive(Diff_UGS_time_series) summary(snaive_model_1) checkresiduals(snaive_model_1)

#exponential smooting, p-value = 9.203e-11, residual SD(sigma)= 0.1281, residuals seem to have a pattern, some acf crosses %95 conf interval boundaries

es_model_2 <- ets(UGS_time_series) summary(es_model_2) checkresiduals(es_model_2)

#ARIMA method, d for eliminating the trend, and D for eliminating seasonality, p-value= 2.971e-11, residual SD= 149799.9 , some acf are out of boundaries, residuals seem to have a strong pattern

arima_model_3 <- auto.arima(UGS_time_series[1:28], d= 1, D= 1) summary(arima_model_3) checkresiduals(arima_model_3)

#linear regression with other independent variables, p-value= 7.027e-09, residual SD= 47250, all acf in the boundaries and relatively have lower values, residuals seem random

lm_model_4 <- lm(UGS[1:28] ~ RNUV[1:28] + NLPG[1:28] + PU[1:28] + PG[1:28] + NUGV[1:28] + NDGV[1:28] + GNP.Agriculture[1:28] + GNP.Commerce[1:28] + GNP.Total[1:28],data_gasoline) summary(lm_model_4) checkresiduals(lm_model_4)

##Residual standard error: 40090 on 18 degrees of freedom ##Multiple R-squared: 0.953, Adjusted R-squared: 0.9295 ##F-statistic: 40.58 on 9 and 18 DF, p-value: 3.879e-10

#define seasonality 
data_gasoline$trend=seq(0,31,by=1)

#define trend 
data_gasoline$quarter=seq(1,4,by=1)

#model with seasonality lm_model_5 <- lm(UGS[1:28] ~ RNUV[1:28] + NLPG[1:28] + PU[1:28] + PG[1:28] + NUGV[1:28] + NDGV[1:28] + GNP.Agriculture[1:28] + GNP.Commerce[1:28] + GNP.Total[1:28] + quarter[1:28],data_gasoline) summary(lm_model_5) checkresiduals(lm_model_5)

##Residual standard error: 38770 on 17 degrees of freedom ##Multiple R-squared: 0.9585, Adjusted R-squared: 0.9341 ##F-statistic: 39.27 on 10 and 17 DF, p-value: 9.187e-10

#model with trend and seasonality lm_model_6 <- lm(UGS[1:28] ~ RNUV[1:28] + NLPG[1:28] + PU[1:28] + PG[1:28] + NUGV[1:28] + NDGV[1:28] + GNP.Agriculture[1:28] + GNP.Commerce[1:28] + GNP.Total[1:28] + quarter[1:28] + trend[1:28],data_gasoline) summary(lm_model_6) checkresiduals(lm_model_6)

##Residual standard error: 37340 on 16 degrees of freedom ##Multiple R-squared: 0.9638, Adjusted R-squared: 0.9389 ##F-statistic: 38.71 on 11 and 16 DF, p-value: 2.07e-09

#define lag 
data_gasoline$lag <- NA 
data_gasoline$lag <- dplyr::lag(data_gasoline$UGS)

#model with trend seasonality and lag variables lm_model_7 <- lm(UGS[1:28] ~ RNUV[1:28] + NLPG[1:28] + PU[1:28] + PG[1:28] + NUGV[1:28] + NDGV[1:28] + GNP.Agriculture[1:28] + GNP.Commerce[1:28] + GNP.Total[1:28] + quarter[1:28] + trend[1:28] + lag[1:28],data_gasoline) summary(lm_model_7) checkresiduals(lm_model_7)

data_gasoline <- as.data.frame(data_gasoline) 
a29 <- predict(lm_model_7,newdata = data_gasoline[29,3:14]) 
a30 <- predict(lm_model_7,newdata = data_gasoline[30,3:14]) 
a31 <- predict(lm_model_7,newdata = data_gasoline[31,3:14]) 
a32 <- predict(lm_model_7,newdata = data_gasoline[32,3:14])
forecast <- c(a29,a30,a31,a32) 
plot(forecast)
